            <h2>Understanding qEEG</h2>

            <p>
                Quantitative Electroencephalography (qEEG) is a sophisticated neuroimaging technique that allows for the precise measurement and analysis of electrical activity in the brain. By placing electrodes on specific scalp locations, we can capture and record brainwave patterns across various frequency bands and brain regions. These patterns are then quantified and analyzed to identify abnormalities or dysregulations in neural activity, providing valuable diagnostic information.

            </p>

            <h2>How qEEG Helps</h2>
            <p>
                We recognize the complexity of brain function and the importance of individualized care. qEEG serves as a cornerstone of our diagnostic process, enabling us to uncover subtle patterns in brain activity that may underlie symptoms of conditions such as attention deficits, mood disorders, anxiety, and cognitive impairments. By gaining a comprehensive understanding of each client's unique brain profile through qEEG analysis, we can tailor our treatment approaches to target specific areas of concern with precision and efficacy.

            </p>


